'''Jacobina''' is a city in the Centro Norte Baiano mesoregion of [[Bahia]]. It was founded July 28, 1722 and the population is 78,842.<ref>[ftp://geoftp.ibge.gov.br/Organizacao/Divisao_Territorial/2008/DTB_2008.zip population data of the municipality]{{dead link|date=July 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} {{in lang|pt}} Retrieved on June 26, 2012</ref><ref>[http://www.ibge.gov.br/home/geociencias/cartografia/default_territ_area.shtm land area] {{in lang|pt}} Retrieved on June 26, 2012</ref><ref>[http://www.ibge.gov.br/home/estatistica/populacao/censo2010/populacao_por_municipio.shtm Statistics on the local geographical] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110516000000/http://www.ibge.gov.br/home/estatistica/populacao/censo2010/populacao_por_municipio.shtm |date=May 16, 2011 }} {{in lang|pt}} Retrieved on June 26, 2012</ref>

Surrounded by [[mountains]], hills, [[lake]]s, [[river]]s, [[Spring (hydrology)|spring]]s, and waterfalls, Jacobina markets itself as a destination for lovers of [[ecological tourism]].{{fact|date=April 2017}} Located in the [[Bahia|northwest region of Bahia]], in the extreme north of the [[Chapada Diamantina]], Jacobina is 330 kilometers from [[Salvador, Bahia|Salvador]] and is also known as 'City of Gold', a legacy of the gold mines which attracted the pioneers from São Paulo in the early seventeenth century.

